[0.013, "o", "\u001b[2;34Hrver configur\u001b[3;10Hration di\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fctives that give the server its instr\u001b[4;33Hrg/docs/2.4/> for detailed infor\u001b[5;8Hrticular\u001b[6;29Hrg/docs/2.4/mod/di\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[7;5H\u001b[m\u000fr a discussion of each configuration di\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[9;18He\u001b[m\u000fad the instructions in he\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000f without under\u001b[10;24H\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f he\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000f only as hints or \u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fminders.  If you a\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000f unsu\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[11;44H\u001b[m\u000fr\u001b[13;10Hration and logfile names: If the filenames you specify for\u001b[14;12Hrver's control files begin with \"/\" (or \"drive:/\" for\u001b[15;5Hrver\u001b[16;28HrverRoot is p\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[17;10H\u001b[m\u000frverRoot set to \"/usr/local/apache2\" will be interp\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[18;5H\u001b[m\u000frver as \"/usr/local/apache2/logs/access_log\", whe\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[19;15H\u001b[m\u000frp\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[22;5H\u001b[m\u000frverRoot: The top of the di\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fctory t\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fe under which the server\u001b[23;10Hration, error, and log files a\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[25;43He\u001b[m\u000fctor\u001b[26;5HrverRoot at a non-local disk, be su\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[27;12He\u001b[m\u000fctive, if file-based mutexes a\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000f used.  If you wish to sha\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[28;10H\u001b[m\u000frverRoot for\u001b[31;3H\u001b[96mrver\u001b[34;66H\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fctor\u001b[35;5Hr individual mutexes, or\u001b[37;31H\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fctory if mutexes a\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[38;17He\u001b[m\u000fctory is not on a local disk or is not appropriate for\u001b[39;7Hr \u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[41;18H\u001b[m\u000fr\u001b[44;56H\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fsses and/or\u001b[45;5Hrts, instead of the default. See also the <Vir\u001b[46;6H\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[48;44He\u001b[49;5He\u001b[m\u000fvent Apache from glomming onto all bound IP add\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[55;183H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f3,19\u001b[56;4H\u001b[?25h"]
