[0.009, "o", "\u001b[1;2H\u001b[70X\r\n# This is the main Apache HTTP server configuration file.  It contains the\u001b[3;2H configuration directives that give the server its instructions.\u001b[4;2H See <URL:http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/> for detailed information.\u001b[5;2H In particular, see \u001b[20X\r\n# <URL:http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/directives.html>\r\n# for a discussion of each configuration directive. \u001b[8;2H\u001b[42X\n Do \u001b[0;10;1m\u000fNOT\u001b[m\u000f simply read the instructions in here without understanding\u001b[10;2H what they do.  They're here only as hints or reminders.  If you are unsure\r\n# consult the online docs. You have been warned.  \r\n#\u001b[50X\r\n# Configuration and logfile names: If the filenames you specify for many\r\n# of the server's control files begin with \"/\" (or \"drive:/\" for Win32), the\r\n# server will use that explicit path.  If the filenames do *not* begin\r\n# with \"/\", the value of ServerRoot is prepended -- so \"logs/access_log\"\u001b[17;2H with ServerRoot set to \"/usr/local/apache2\" will be interpreted by the\u001b[18;2H server as \"/usr/local/apache2/logs/access_log\", whereas \"/logs/access_log\" \u001b[19;2H will be interpreted as '/logs/access_log'.\u001b[13X\r\n\u001b[56X\n#\u001b[39X\n ServerRoot: The top of the directory tree under which the server's\u001b[23;2H configuration, error, and log files are kept.  \u001b[24;2H\u001b[48X\r\n# Do not add a slash at the end of the directory path.  If you point\r\n# ServerRoot at a non-local disk, be sure to specify a local disk on the\r\n# Mutex directive, if file-based mutexes are used.  If you wish to share the\r\n# same ServerRoot for multiple httpd daemons, you will need to change at\r\n# least PidFile.\u001b[7X\r\n\n\u001b[96mServerRoot\u001b[m\u000f \u001b[92m\"/etc/httpd\"\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[46X\r\n\u001b[47X\u001b[34;3HMutex: Allows you to set the mutex mechanism and mutex file directory\u001b[35;3Hfor individual mutexes, or change the global defaults\u001b[15X\u001b[36;2H\u001b[45X\n Uncomment and change the directory if mutexes are file-based and the default\r\n# mutex file directory is not on a local disk or is not appropriate for some\r\n# other reason.\r\n#\r\n# Mutex default:/run/httpd\u001b[43;2H\u001b[28X\n Listen: Allows you to bind Apache to specific IP addresses and/or\u001b[45;3Hports, instead of the default. See also the <VirtualHost>\u001b[10X\u001b[46;3Hdirective.\u001b[53X\u001b[47;2H\u001b[66X\u001b[48;3HChange this to Listen on specific IP addresses as shown below to \u001b[49;2H prevent Apache from glomming onto all bound IP addresses.\u001b[50;2H\u001b[68X\nListen 12.34.56.78:80\u001b[43X\r\n\u001b[96mListen\u001b[m\u000f 80\u001b[20X\r\n \r\n#\u001b[55;184H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f,1            Top\u001b[56;17H\u001b[?25h"]
[9.799, "o", "\u001b[?25l\b\u001b[m\u000f \b"]
[0.011, "o", "\u001b[1;2HLoadModule lbmethod_heartbeat_module modules/mod_lbmethod_heartbeat.so\r\n\u001b[96mLoadModule\u001b[m\u000f unixd_module modules/mod_unixd.so\u001b[30X\u001b[3;2HLoadModule heartbeat_module modules/mod_heartbeat.so\u001b[12X\u001b[4;2HLoadModule heartmonitor_module modules/mod_heartmonitor.so\u001b[12X\u001b[5;2HLoadModule dav_module modules/mod_dav.so\r\n\u001b[96mLoadModule\u001b[m\u000f status_module modules/mod_status.so\u001b[14X\r\n\u001b[96mLoadModule\u001b[m\u000f autoindex_module modules/mod_autoindex.so\u001b[8;2HLoadModule asis_module modules/mod_asis.so\u001b[9;2HLoadModule info_module modules/mod_info.so\u001b[24X\u001b[10;2HLoadModule suexec_module modules/mod_suexec.so\u001b[29X\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f<IfModule\u001b[m\u000f !mpm_prefork_module\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f>\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[20X\r\n        #LoadModule cgid_module modules/mod_cgid.so\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f</IfModule>\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[61X\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f<IfModule\u001b[m\u000f mpm_prefork_module\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f>\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[47X\r\n        #LoadModule cgi_module modules/mod_cgi.so\u001b[21X\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f</IfModule>\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[61X\u001b[17;2HLoadModule dav_fs_module modules/mod_dav_fs.so\u001b[25X\u001b[18;2HLoadModule dav_lock_module modules/mod_dav_lock.so\u001b[26X\u001b[19;2HLoadModule vhost_alias_module modules/mod_vhost_alias.so\r\n\u001b[96mLoadModule\u001b[m\u000f negotiation_module modules/mod_negotiation.so\r\n\u001b[96mLoadModule\u001b[m\u000f dir_module modules/mod_dir.so\u001b[22;2HLoadModule imagemap_module modules/mod_imagemap.so\u001b[17X\u001b[23;2HLoadModule actions_module modules/mod_actions.so\u001b[24;2HLoadModule speling_module modules/mod_speling.so\r\n\u001b[96mLoadModule\u001b[m\u000f userdir_module modules/mod_userdir.so\u001b[20X\r\n\u001b[96mLoadModule\u001b[m\u000f alias_module modules/mod_alias.so\u001b[28X\r\n\u001b[96mLoadModule\u001b[m\u000f \u001b[30m\u001b[103mrewrite_module\u001b[m\u000f modules/mod_rewrite.so\u001b[28X\r\n\u001b[72X\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f<IfModule\u001b[m\u000f unixd_module\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f>\r\n\n\u001b[m\u000f# If you wish httpd to run as a different user or group, you must run\r\n# httpd as root initially and it will switch.  \u001b[34;3HUser/Group: The name (or #number) of the user/group to run httpd as. \u001b[35;3HIt is usually good practice to create a dedicated user and group for\u001b[36;2H running httpd, as with most system services.\u001b[37;2H\u001b[77X\r\n\u001b[96mUser\u001b[m\u000f http\u001b[67X\r\n\u001b[96mGroup\u001b[m\u000f http\u001b[5X\r\n \r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f</IfModule>\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[15X\u001b[43;2H 'Main' server configuration\u001b[44;2H\u001b[66X\u001b[45;3HThe directives in this section set up the values used by the 'main'\u001b[46;3Hserver, which responds to any requests that aren't handled by a\u001b[47;2H <VirtualHost> definition.  These values also provide defaults for\u001b[48;3Hany <VirtualHost> containers you may define later in the file.   \u001b[49;2H\u001b[58X\n All of these directives may appear inside <VirtualHost> containers,\u001b[51;2H in which case these default settings will be overridden for the\r\n# virtual host being defined.\r\n#\r\n \u001b[55;184H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f89,12         32%\u001b[56;16H\u001b[?25h"]
