[0.012, "o", "\u001b[1;2H\u001b[70X\r\n# This is the main Apache HTTP server configuration file.  It contains the\u001b[3;2H configuration di\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fctives that give the server its instructions.\u001b[4;2H See <URL:http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/> for detailed information.\u001b[5;2H In particular, see \u001b[20X\r\n# <URL:http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/di\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fctives.html>\r\n# for a discussion of each configuration di\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fctive. \u001b[8;2H\u001b[42X\n Do \u001b[0;10;1m\u000fNOT\u001b[m\u000f simply \u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fad the instructions in he\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000f without understanding\u001b[10;2H what they do.  They'\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000f he\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000f only as hints or \u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fminders.  If you a\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000f unsu\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\r\n\u001b[m\u000f# consult the online docs. You have been warned.  \r\n#\u001b[50X\r\n# Configuration and logfile names: If the filenames you specify for many\r\n# of the server's control files begin with \"/\" (or \"drive:/\" for Win32), the\r\n# server will use that explicit path.  If the filenames do *not* begin\r\n# with \"/\", the value of ServerRoot is p\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fpended -- so \"logs/access_log\"\u001b[17;2H with ServerRoot set to \"/usr/local/apache2\" will be interp\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fted by the\u001b[18;2H server as \"/usr/local/apache2/logs/access_log\", whe\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fas \"/logs/access_log\" \u001b[19;2H will be interp\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fted as '/logs/access_log'.\u001b[13X\r\n\u001b[56X\n#\u001b[39X\n ServerRoot: The top of the di\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fctory t\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fe under which the server's\u001b[23;2H configuration, error, and log files a\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000f kept.  \u001b[24;2H\u001b[48X\r\n# Do not add a slash at the end of the di\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fctory path.  If you point\r\n# ServerRoot at a non-local disk, be su\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000f to specify a local disk on the\r\n# Mutex di\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fctive, if file-based mutexes a\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000f used.  If you wish to sha\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000f the\r\n# same ServerRoot for multiple httpd daemons, you will need to change at\r\n# least PidFile.\u001b[7X\r\n\n\u001b[96mServerRoot\u001b[m\u000f \u001b[92m\"/etc/httpd\"\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[46X\r\n\u001b[47X\u001b[34;3HMutex: Allows you to set the mutex mechanism and mutex file di\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fctory\u001b[35;3Hfor individual mutexes, or change the global defaults\u001b[15X\u001b[36;2H\u001b[45X\n Uncomment and change the di\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fctory if mutexes a\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000f file-based and the default\r\n# mutex file di\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fctory is not on a local disk or is not appropriate for some\r\n# other \u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fason.\r\n#\r\n# Mutex default:/run/httpd\u001b[43;2H\u001b[28X\n Listen: Allows you to bind Apache to specific IP add\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fsses and/or\u001b[45;3Hports, instead of the default. See also the <VirtualHost>\u001b[10X\u001b[46;3Hdi\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fctive.\u001b[53X\u001b[47;2H\u001b[66X\u001b[48;3HChange this to Listen on specific IP add\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fsses as shown below to \u001b[49;2H p\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fvent Apache from glomming onto all bound IP add\u001b[30m\u001b[103mre\u001b[m\u000fsses.\u001b[50;2H\u001b[68X\nListen 12.34.56.78:80\u001b[43X\r\n\u001b[96mListen\u001b[m\u000f 80\u001b[20X\r\n \r\n#\u001b[55;183H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f3,19           Top\u001b[56;4H\u001b[?25h"]
